    "description": {
        "en-US": "Adds more customization options to YouTube subtitles. Fully compatible with existing YouTube subtitles, as it merely changes their appearance using CSS and does not replace them.\n\nAccess the options as you normally would in the browser, or you can set up hotkeys to trigger certain options in your browser's keyboard shortcuts menu.\n\nList of available options:\n\n<b>Font options:</b>\n<ul><li>Custom font name</li><li>Font size</li><li>Font weight</li><li>Font color</li><li>Font opacity</li></ul>\n<b>Text options:</b>\n<ul><li>Letter spacing</li><li>Word spacing</li><li>Line height</li><li>Text position</li><li>Text margin from edge</li><li>Text transform</li><li>Text stroke</li><li>Text shadow</li><li>Text blur</li></ul>\n<b>Background options:</b>\n<ul><li>Background type</li><li>Background color and opacity</li><li>Background padding</li><li>Background radius</li></ul>"
    },
